** Saunders Automation ** is a control system engineering specialist, specializing in the design and commissioning of PLC, SCADA, and RTU systems, electrical engineering, TUV functional safety and energy management systems. 

With ongoing success in the field of control systems engineering ** Saunders
Automation ** are proud to present opportunities to ** Graduate Control
Systems Engineers ** located in the Brisbane area looking to be treated as
more than just a number or a commodity. In the modern engineering world our
focus is on nurturing flexibility for our staff and customers alike. This
means maintaining proven engineering methods whilst thinking outside of the
square to deliver exciting projects. We are continually looking to remain on
the forefront of the industry and technology.

** The responsibilities of the role include but are not limited to: **

  * Programming of PLC and SCADA control systems or similar industrial software environments. 
  * Gain experience with Schneider, Siemens or Allen Bradley. 
  * You will undertake configuration or programming of any typical industrial device that you might find in, or alongside, a control system: Variable Speed Drives (VSDs), protocol converters, network switches, protection relays etc. 
  * Understand and program with common industrial communication protocols such as Modbus RTU/TCP and Ethernet/IP. 
  * Understand physical installation of control systems including basic electrical installation and safety knowledge. 
  * Undertake testing both on the bench, in the factory, and on site. 

** To be successful in the role you will have the ability to demonstrate the following: **

  * Knowledge of programming of PLC and SCADA control systems or similar industrial software environments. 
  * Demonstrate experience in fault finding and support for control, electrical, and instrumentation systems. 
  * Understand and interpret electrical drawings, design specifications and IO schedules. 
  * Undertake development of design drawings and specifications. 
  * Communicate effectively within a team environment. 
  * Manage yourself and sometimes others to deliver project scope in line with contract and schedule. 

** Job challenges include: **

  * Operate effectively in a team environment where every day can present a fresh challenge. 
  * Establish and maintain relationships both externally and internally. 
  * Ensure jobs are on time, budget and per the agreed scope of works. 
  * Communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical people alike. 
  * Maintain statutory compliance across all jobs. 
  * Keep up to date with constant change across the control system and technologies field. 
  * Obtain and maintain engineering qualifications and certifications as required by the company. 

** THE BENEFITS **

  * The opportunity to work on a unique industrial transformation project. 
  * Excellent work environment 
  * Market competitive salary 
  * Supportive Culture 
  * Cost of Living Discounts 
  * Wellbeing Leave days 
  * Paid Parental Leave 

** Saunders Automation ** pride ourselves on the quality of work and our enjoyable work environment, with the majority of work being performed in an office environment or sites within the Brisbane region. We support and encourage our staff with ongoing professional development to further our business and the careers of our staff. If you meet the requirements above and would be excited to join our team please submit your application with us. 

Saunders embraces the values of an innovative and diverse workforce and
recognises that inclusion sets everyone up for success. All suitably qualified
or experienced applicants will be considered.

** HOW TO APPLY **

Please click the apply button and upload a copy of your resume. The successful
applicant will be required to provide contactable references, submit personal
data for a criminal record check, and undergo a pre-employment medical,
including a drug and alcohol test.

